Day 9: Deployment and Services types, label and selector matchLabels, coredns and DNS table explained, /etc/resolve.conf
Day 10: port targetport logic, labels - selectors logic, service type: loadbalancer explained
*Day 11: service type explained deeply, diff betn load balancer and ingress controller, 
*Day 12: headless service type explained in detail, using headless with statefulsets for database hosting on k8s, 
        stateful set: f/w traffic to one pod only (primary), and the second pod acts as a replica.

Headless service type doesn't get ip address assigned, it only has dns name of svc (svc-name.ns.svc.cluster.local), hence, svc has been listed with all pod IPs in DNS utils (nslookup).
But in clusterIP service, svc do get IP address and that SVC IP Address is listed with svc's dns name (svc-name.ns.svc.cluster.local)

Day 13: Ingress Controller not supported.

Day 14: Deployment Explained, kubectl rollout history, kubectl annotate deployment (for adding change cause), manual version controlling for k8s, max unavailable & maxsurge,
Day 15: deployment strategies, 

